&lt;h2 id="-reverse-proxy"&gt;ğŸ”„ Reverse Proxy
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reverse Proxy&lt;/strong&gt; is an intermediary server that receives requests from clients and forwards them to appropriate backend servers. It helps with load balancing, caching, security, and SSL termination.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ğŸ”¹ Helps hide backend server information to enhance security.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ğŸ”¹ Supports traffic distribution and application performance optimization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="-example-reverse-proxy-configuration-with-nginx"&gt;ğŸ” Example Reverse Proxy configuration with Nginx:
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
